<HEAD>Pleads Guilty to Swallowing 40 Bags of Heroin to Bring to U.S.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Nigerian now living in Boston has pleaded guilty
to drug smuggling by swallowing 40 bags of heroin while visiting
his native land and then flying to the United States, prosecutors
said.
   Collins E. Olloh, 36, pleaded guilty in federal court Monday to
importing more than 100 grams of heroin, authorities said.
   Sentencing was set for Dec. 19. He faces up to 40 years in
prison and a $2 million fine.
   When he arrived in Boston on May 24 on a flight from Nigeria, he
was detained and his luggage searched because his background and
appearance were ``consistent with a narcotics smuggler,'' according
to an affidavit signed by drug agent Felice M. Muollo Jr.
   After refusing to submit to a physical examination or X-ray, he
eventually told customs officials that he had swallowed the bags of
heroin. The bags contained about 230 grams of heroin, said a
statement from the Justice Department.
