<SECOND>PM-Quake-County-Glance, 1st Ld-Writethru,a0621,0370</SECOND>
<HEAD>County-by-County Damages, Deaths and Injuries</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 3rd graf, San Francisco ...' to UPDATE number of deaths
to nine sted eight and injuries to more than 200 sted 100.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a county-by-county summary of death, injury and damage
reports from Tuesday's earthquake as gathered from the California
Office of Emergency Services, other agencies and reporter
observations:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ALAMEDA COUNTY (Oakland and communities east of San Francisco
Bay) _ Mile-long section of upper deck of Interstate 880 collapsed.
The OES and California Highway Patrol reported 253 deaths and 400
injured.
   SAN FRANCISCO _ Nine deaths and more than 200 injured. Block of
apartments destroyed by fire. Several older apartments collapsed.
San Francisco Bay Bridge damaged on Oakland leg. Widespread window
damage. Numerous facades fallen. Power outage. Reports of looting
and assaults.
   SAN MATEO COUNTY (borders San Francisco to south) _ No deaths,
108 injuries, mostly heart and anxiety problems. Seven injured in
wall collapse at Amfac Hotel in Burlingame. Substantial damage at
Hall of Justice in Redwood City, part of a supermarket roof
collapsed. San Mateo bridge over San Francisco Bay 10 miles south
of Candlestick Pak closed for inspection. Dumbarton Bridge across
bay about 30 miles south of San Francisco, also closed.
   SANTA CRUZ COUNTY (south of San Francisco and San Mateo) _ Eight
deaths reported in Santa Cruz. Buildings and houses burned or
collapsed. Highway 1 closed by bridge collapse, houses lost to
fires and landslides. Mountain passes closed by landslides and
fissures in roads. Eight injuries and extensive damage in
Watsonville, east of Santa Cruz. County government without power.
Major structural damage in Scotts Valley.
   SANTA CLARA COUNTY (southeast end of San Francisco Bay) _ One
San Jose resident died of heart attack.
   SAN BENITO COUNTY (south and east of Santa Cruz) _ No deaths.
Forty minor injuries. Numerous buildings collapsed. Roof of a J.C.
Penney department store in Hollister collapsed. Highway 101 closed
by bridge collapse. Power outage throughout county. Water mains
damaged.
   MONTEREY COUNTY (south of Santa Cruz) _ Minor damage reports.
County declared state of emergency.
   MARIN COUNTY (north of San Francisco across Golden Gate) _ Minor
damage.
</TEXT>
