<HEAD>Parliament Lifts Ban on Leading Newspaper Chain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Parliament has lifted a 4-month-old ban
prohibiting Kenya's leading newspaper chain from reporting on the
legislative body because it said the newspaper group had reformed
its editorial policies.
   Parliament banned the Nation Group of newspapers from
parliamentary reporting June 28, claiming it was anti-government
and subversive.
   On Tuesday, members of Parliament said they believed the
newspaper group had instituted sufficient reforms and should be
allowed to return to reporting on the legislature.
   Immediately after the ban was lifted, Nation Group reporters
resumed their seats in the press gallery.
   The group includes three Swahili-language newspapers and two
English-language newspapers, including Kenya's most popular
newspaper, the Daily Nation, which claims a daily readership of
about 250,000 people.
