<HEAD>Record $6.6 Million Holdup in Belgian Post Office</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHARLEROI, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two armed men held up the central post
office of this southern industrial city Wednesday and got away with
a record $6.6 million, police reported.
   Police said the men entered the post office at 9:23 a.m. through
the garage at the back of the building, passed a guard and security
doors, and confronted employees who had just stacked into safes
money brought from the Belgian National Bank.
   The men acted ``professionally,'' police said, adding that a
post office employee may have tipped them off about the large
delivery of money.
   It was the biggest holdup ever reported in Belgium.
