<FIRST>r a AM-Hagman     10-18 0197</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Hagman,0202</SECOND>
<HEAD>Actor's Half-Brother Waives Extradition to Texas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAS VEGAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The half-brother of actor Larry Hagman waived
extradition to Texas on Wednesday to face a charge of
misapplication of funds.
   Gary Hagman, a lawyer from Weatherford, Texas, was reported
missing Sept. 26 and taken into custody Tuesday as he tried to
retrieve a car from the parking lot of a hotel on the Las Vegas
Strip.
   Hagman, 48, who shares a father with the actor, was charged Oct.
2 in Weatherford with misapplication of fiduciary funds.
Weatherford officials would not provide details on the charge,
except to say it stemmed from a complaint from a financial
institution.
   Hagman, in handcuffs and jail clothing, waived extradition
during a brief appearance before state District Judge Donald Mosley.
   Two Weatherford investigators came to Las Vegas to follow up
reports that Hagman had been sighted last week in a casino,
Weatherford police Capt. Raymond Pritchard said Wednesday. The
investigators were to return Hagman to Weatherford after the
necessary paperwork was complete, Pritchard said.
   The charge against Hagman is a second-degree felony that carries
a prison term of 2 to 20 years and a fine of up to $10,000.
