<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--LarchmontGunfight     10-18 0148</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Larchmont Gunfight,0150</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gun Belt Takes Bullet Meant For Policeman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LARCHMONT, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A policeman's gun belt took a bullet
fired at the officer by a car theft suspect he was chasing, police
said. The officer returned fire, killing the man.
   The shooting Tuesday night was a rarity in this small, affluent
village less than 10 miles north of New York City, where car thefts
and burglaries are the most common crimes.
   Officer Michael Walsh stopped a car that had been reported
stolen, and was questioning its two occupants when one of them ran
off, said police Capt. Michael Garcia.
   Officer Timothy Brennan gave chase. The fleeing suspect fired a
.45-caliber pistol at the officer, but the shot hit his gun belt
and Brennan was not injured, Garcia said.
   Brennan, 25, returned fire and hit the man, who ran a short
distance and collapsed, Garcia said.
</TEXT>
