<FIRST>r f BC-Britain-Jaguar     10-18 0199</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Jaguar,0207</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jaguar Hopes To Announce GM Deal Within A Month</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The British luxury car maker Jaguar PLC said
Wednesday it hopes to announce within a month an agreement with
General Motors Corp. under which the U.S. automaker would buy a
minority stake in Jaguar.
   Jaguar has negotiated with GM for several weeks over a possible
cooperation agreement that might thwart a potential buyout bid for
the British firm by Ford Motor Co.
   ``Providing the discussions continue to go well and are
successful, I would be disappointed if we could not be in the
position to put something to our shareholders in the next month,''
Jaguar Chairman John Egan said.
   Jaguar has said it is not interested in being taken over by Ford
or any other car maker, and would prefer a cooperation agreement
with another company.
   Egan, who made his remarks to reporters at a British motor
industry show, said he has not received an approach from Ford since
mid-September, when Ford announced its intention to take a 15
percent stake as a possible prelude to a full bid.
   On Tuesday, Ford said it raised its Jaguar stake to 10.4 percent
from 5 percent.
</TEXT>
