<SECOND>AM-Kodak Camera,0102</SECOND>
<HEAD>Introduce Wide-Angle Disposable in US</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eastman Kodak Co. will introduce a
disposable wide-angle-lens camera in the United States, the company
announced Wednesday.
   The Kodak Stretch 35 will cost $12.95 and enable the user to
take 12 color photographs measuring 3{ inches by 10 inches, Kodak
said.
   The camera will be taken intact to specially equipped processing
centers for film development.
   Eastman Kodak introduced the one-time use camera in Europe and
Japan earlier this year.
   The camera's wide-angle lens will allow users to supplement
their regular pictures with panoramic shots.
</TEXT>
