<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Beazer     10-18 0148</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Beazer,0157</SECOND>
<HEAD>Beazer Posts Big Profit Gain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Beazer PLC, a British building materials and
construction company, on Wednesday reported a 22 percent jump in
after-tax profit for its latest financial year, helped largely by
contributions from its U.S. unit, Koppers Co.
   Beazer said after-tax profit for the year ended June 30 came to
$147 million, or 92.6 million pounds, compared with $120 million a
year earlier.
   Earnings per share came to 48 cents, up from 39 cents.
   Sales for the year jumped 47 percent to $3.1 billion from $2.1
billion.
   Beazer said its strong performance in the 1988-89 fiscal year
was due to a strong input from Koppers and a sturdy performance in
the British housing and property market.
   Beazer acquired Koppers Co. last year.
   The British company did not break out quarterly or half-year
results. It is not required to under British law.
</TEXT>
