<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Wang     10-18 0179</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Wang,0188</SECOND>
<HEAD>Wang Laboratories Reports Expected First-Quarter Loss</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOWELL, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wang Laboratories Inc. reported an expected
first-quarter loss Wednesday, as the struggling computer maker
showed the effects of a slowdown in the computer industry.
   Wang officials reported a first-quarter net loss Wednesday of
$62.1 million, or 38 cents per share, compared with net earnings of
$13.1 million, or 8 cents per share, during the same period last
year.
   The latest quarter's loss includes a $12.9 million, pre-tax
restructuring charge to cover the costs of employee severance
packages. The year-earlier quarter included a $3.1 million loss
from discontinued operations.
   Revenue for the first quarter was $596.8 million, down almost 13
percent from a restated $684 million during the same period last
year, Wang officials reported.
   ``The first quarter's results should not be a surprise to
anyone, and certainly there will be another loss in the second
quarter,'' said Richard W. Miller, Wang's president and chief
operating officer.
   However, he said he expected the company to return to
profitability in its fourth fiscal quarter, which ends next June.
</TEXT>
